# stewardship nightly cron template
#
# Install:
#   1. Set PLUGIN_PATH to the absolute path of the stewardship plugin dir
#      (the directory that contains scripts/drift_check.py).
#   2. Substitute the placeholder, then append the line to your crontab:
#
#       PLUGIN_PATH="$HOME/.claude/plugins/stewardship"
#       LINE="0 3 * * * /usr/bin/env python3 \"$PLUGIN_PATH/scripts/drift_check.py\" >> \"$HOME/.local/share/stewardship-plugin/logs/nightly.log\" 2>&1 && /usr/bin/env python3 \"$PLUGIN_PATH/scripts/auto_memory_housekeep.py\" >> \"$HOME/.local/share/stewardship-plugin/logs/nightly.log\" 2>&1"
#       (crontab -l 2>/dev/null; echo "$LINE") | crontab -
#
# Remove:
#   Filter the stewardship line back out:
#       crontab -l | grep -v 'stewardship' | crontab -
#
# Notes:
# - "0 3 * * *" runs at 03:00 local time daily (cron uses the system timezone
#   configured in /etc/timezone or TZ= at the top of crontab).
# - To pass --apply to auto_memory_housekeep, add it after the script path.
# - To run drift_check on a custom context dir, add --dir /path/to/context.
# - LOG_DIR is created by the script on first run if it does not exist; ensure
#   the parent directory is writable.
# - Use `crontab -e` to edit interactively, or `crontab -l` to verify.
#
# ─── Template line (replace PLUGIN_PATH and LOG_DIR before use) ────────────
0 3 * * * /usr/bin/env python3 "PLUGIN_PATH/scripts/drift_check.py" >> "LOG_DIR/nightly.log" 2>&1 && /usr/bin/env python3 "PLUGIN_PATH/scripts/auto_memory_housekeep.py" >> "LOG_DIR/nightly.log" 2>&1
